Real Madrid may likely be without playmaker, Isco, when they tackle Villarreal in the La Liga fixture on Sunday at El Madridgal Stadium. The Spain international sustained a muscular injury in his right femoral biceps ahead of the encounter. A club statement on Wednesday read: “After the tests carried out today by the Real Madrid Medical Services, our player Isco has been diagnosed with a muscular injury in the right femoral biceps. “His recovery will continue to be monitored.” Real Madrid head to the game after playing a 1-1 draw with Valladolid at the Santiago Bernabeu last weekend. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.